22std::vector<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits> ToResolutionBitrateLimits(
23 const std::vector<EncoderInfoSettings::BitrateLimit>& limits) {
24 std::vector<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits> result;
25 for (const auto& limit : limits) {
26 result.push_back(VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits(
27 limit.frame_size_pixels, limit.min_start_bitrate_bps,
28 limit.min_bitrate_bps, limit.max_bitrate_bps));
29 }
30 return result;
31}
32
33} // namespace
34
35// Default bitrate limits for simulcast with one active stream:
36// {frame_size_pixels, min_start_bitrate_bps, min_bitrate_bps, max_bitrate_bps}.
37std::vector<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits>
38EncoderInfoSettings::GetDefaultSinglecastBitrateLimits(
39 VideoCodecType codec_type) {
40 // Specific limits for VP9. Other codecs use VP8 limits.
41 if (codec_type == kVideoCodecVP9) {
42 return {{320 * 180, 0, 30000, 150000},
43 {480 * 270, 120000, 30000, 300000},
44 {640 * 360, 190000, 30000, 420000},
45 {960 * 540, 350000, 30000, 1000000},
46 {1280 * 720, 480000, 30000, 1500000}};
47 }
48
49 return {{320 * 180, 0, 30000, 300000},
50 {480 * 270, 200000, 30000, 500000},
51 {640 * 360, 300000, 30000, 800000},
52 {960 * 540, 500000, 30000, 1500000},
53 {1280 * 720, 900000, 30000, 2500000}};
54}
55
56absl::optional<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits>
57EncoderInfoSettings::GetDefaultSinglecastBitrateLimitsForResolution(
58 VideoCodecType codec_type,
59 int frame_size_pixels) {
60 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo info;
61 info.resolution_bitrate_limits =
62 GetDefaultSinglecastBitrateLimits(codec_type);
63 return info.GetEncoderBitrateLimitsForResolution(frame_size_pixels);
64}
65
66EncoderInfoSettings::EncoderInfoSettings(std::string name)
67 : requested_resolution_alignment_("requested_resolution_alignment"),
68 apply_alignment_to_all_simulcast_layers_(
69 "apply_alignment_to_all_simulcast_layers") {
70 FieldTrialStructList<BitrateLimit> bitrate_limits(
71 {FieldTrialStructMember(
72 "frame_size_pixels",
73 [](BitrateLimit* b) { return &b->frame_size_pixels; }),
74 FieldTrialStructMember(
75 "min_start_bitrate_bps",
76 [](BitrateLimit* b) { return &b->min_start_bitrate_bps; }),
77 FieldTrialStructMember(
78 "min_bitrate_bps",
79 [](BitrateLimit* b) { return &b->min_bitrate_bps; }),
80 FieldTrialStructMember(
81 "max_bitrate_bps",
82 [](BitrateLimit* b) { return &b->max_bitrate_bps; })},
83 {});
84
85 if (field_trial::FindFullName(name).empty()) {
86 // Encoder name not found, use common string applying to all encoders.
87 name = "WebRTC-GetEncoderInfoOverride";
88 }
89
90 ParseFieldTrial({&bitrate_limits, &requested_resolution_alignment_,
91 &apply_alignment_to_all_simulcast_layers_},
92 field_trial::FindFullName(name));
93
94 resolution_bitrate_limits_ = ToResolutionBitrateLimits(bitrate_limits.Get());
95}
96
97absl::optional<int> EncoderInfoSettings::requested_resolution_alignment()
98 const {
99 if (requested_resolution_alignment_ &&
100 requested_resolution_alignment_.Value() < 1) {
101 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported alignment value, ignored.";
102 return absl::nullopt;
103 }
104 return requested_resolution_alignment_.GetOptional();
105}
